---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Prose from '../components/Prose.astro';

---

<BaseLayout
	title="About Me"
	description="About Warongkon - Software Developer with 4 years of experience"
>
  <div class='container'>
		<main class='prose text-lg dark:prose-invert'>
      <article>
        <div class='w-full md:flex md:items-center gap-16 mb-10'>
          <div class="text-pretty leading-9">
            <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">About Me</h1>
            <Prose>
              <div class="text-lg">
                <p>Hi, I’m <strong>Warongkon</strong> – a passionate Software Developer dedicated to building efficient, scalable, and high-performance solutions. As of 2026, I have accumulated 4 years of professional experience in the software industry.</p>
              </div>
            </Prose>
          </div>
        </div>     
        <div>
          <p>
            I am a problem-solver who enjoys tackling complex challenges with clean and effective code. While my expertise lies heavily within the Microsoft ecosystem, I maintain the flexibility to adapt and employ the best tools for any given task.
          </p>

          <h2>My Professional Journey</h2>
          <p>
            My journey into professional software development began in 2022. Over the past 4 years, I have honed my skills by developing web applications using <strong>C#</strong> and <strong>Angular</strong>. I have contributed to enterprise-level projects where performance, security, and maintainability are paramount.
          </p>

          <h2>Skills & Expertise</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Backend Development:</strong> Expert in building RESTful APIs using ASP.NET Core and implementing comprehensive Unit Testing.</li>
            <li><strong>Frontend Development:</strong> Crafting responsive and interactive web interfaces with Angular, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS.</li>
            <li><strong>Database Management:</strong> Designing and optimizing both SQL Server and MongoDB databases.</li>
            <li><strong>Software Engineering:</strong> Applying SOLID principles, Clean Code, and Design Patterns to ensure software quality and longevity.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Goals for 2026</h2>
          <p>
            In 2026, I am focused on deepening my expertise in <strong>System Design</strong> and integrating <strong>AI-driven tools</strong> to enhance the development lifecycle. I am also exploring <strong>Microservices Architecture</strong> to better handle the complexities of modern, distributed systems.
          </p>

          <p>
            I firmly believe that "learning is a lifelong journey." This blog serves as a digital journal where I document my findings and share knowledge with the community. Thank you for stopping by and getting to know me!
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </main>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
